    "created_at": "2016-05-20T03:57:14Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-20T03:57:49Z",
    "body": "@danhp thanks for looking into it! So the reason I mentioned it in the first place is because I think it'd be a good idea to be able to show a popup panel on mouse down instead of mouse up. By using mouse down, by the time the user lifts their finger from the button, the panel would already be visible, making the app feel much faster.\n\nIf you hold the mouse button down over a native OSX menu bar app, the panels show up on mouse down (not mouse up) so I was trying to replicate that behaviour as close as I could.\n"
  },
