    "created_at": "2016-05-20T13:28:55Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-05-20T13:32:05Z",
    "body": "@keithpitt Yup, that's the reason I looked into this (wanted the tray to behave like native). But exposing a `mouse-down` event won't bring it closer to being solved as it will allow you to show a menu but not highlight the tray icon itself. So it's better to just let the app handle all of that for you. As for having it show on `mouseDown`, long presses leave the tray icon highlighted until the next click but with no menu showing.\n\nFor reference the Google Drive tray runs into a very similar problem but overcomes it by having a custom menu that they have full control over.\n"
  },
